properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 30 at 1:59PM MST until February 1 at 12:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High Wind Watch for the Cody Foothills Friday night and
Saturday Morning...

.Favorable weather conditions will develop over the Cody Foothills
for strong westerly winds to occur Friday night into Saturday
morning.

* WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Cody Foothills. The strongest winds will occur just
south of Cody, as well as between Clark and junction of Highway
120 and the Chief Joseph Highway.

* WHEN...From Friday evening through Saturday morning. The
strongest winds are expected between 4 AM and 9 AM Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Enhanced blow over risk for
light and high profile vehicles especially along highway 120.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY EVENING THROUGH SATURDAY MORNING
